cs.CG, cs.NA, cs.SC, cs.SY, cs.DS 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CG (Computational Geometry) - The paper deals with computing an isotopic polygonal approximation to a curve, which is a problem in computational geometry. 
2. cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) - The paper uses numerical methods and interval arithmetic to compute the approximation, which falls under the scope of numerical analysis. 
3. cs.SC (Symbolic Computation) - The paper deals with algebraic curves and their singularities, which is a topic in symbolic computation. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper uses a computational model to compute the approximation, which can be seen as a control system. 
5. cs.DS (Dynamical Systems) - The paper deals with the behavior of curves under subdivision algorithms, which can be seen as a dynamical system.
